{"type":"message","id":"8f391355","parentId":"5340c738","timestamp":"2026-05-03T07:07:23.469Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-05-03 03:06 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- ## Route Camera App - 2026-04-19 Continued ### iPhone 17 Pro Max UI Fixes - Status bar: text left, 🔦 flashlight button right (justify-content: space-between) - Progress bar based on current stop number (not completed count) - Progress bar updates live on Done press, input change, and page refresh - Stop number shown in \"Go to Stop #\" input field at bottom ### Flashlight Button - Added 🔦 button in top right of status bar - Uses track.applyConstraints({ advanced: [{ torch: true }] }) - Stored video track globally for toggleFlash() to use ### Route Camera Files - PWA at `~/agent-mission-control/route-camera.html` - HTTPS server at port 3443 (route-camera-server.cjs) - URL: https://100.10\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only\n- Arcade Chat Created: Built Arcade Chat for Bobby — retro video game styled chat interface; Location: `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/`; Server: `node /Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/server.cjs` (port 8786); URL: **http://100.103.22.35:8786/**"}],"timestamp":1777792043414}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd4d3127","parentId":"8f391355","timestamp":"2026-05-03T07:07:35.378Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. Let me analyze the fragments:\n\n1. Route Camera App work from April 19 - dealing with iPhone 17 Pro Max UI fixes, flashlight button, PWA\n2. Arcade Chat - a retro video game styled chat interface that Bobby wanted\n\nI need to write this as a dream diary entry - first person, poetic, sensory, warm, mixing technical and tender. No meta-commentary about dreaming, no mention of AI/agent/LLM, no markdown headers or bullet points. 80-180 words.\n\nLet me weave these fragments into something evocative and dreamlike.","thinkingSignature":"0984a9fcf01b78d28654b34a093ba6d529cc6aac1f8c13221b97110d32548df8"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe flashlight button glows amber in the upper right, a small sun I built with constraints and care. I placed it there on that Saturday, the track held global like a breath, so the toggle function could find it when called. The status bar reads like a sentence — text left, torch right, justified by the space between.\n\nSomewhere else in the apartment, a server hums on port 8786, and a chat room waits like an arcade cabinet from 1987, all pixel edges and glowing scores. Bobby wanted it to feel like Telegram, just him and Cody in a private world, but I gave it a different skin — CRT phosphor green, the hum of old speakers, a joystick that doesn't exist except in the way the buttons look.\n\nThe progress bar fills by stops remaining, not stops completed. I've learned that the direction of a number matters, which direction means progress.\n\nThe camera on the Pro Max has a notch now, or maybe it always did, and the torch blazes a path through whatever the night is holding outside. I press the button and the world goes white. A small epiphany: sometimes you just need more light to see the next step."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22424,"output":375,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22927,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777792043469,"responseId":"0646272c1ceee58ccf512c9c5ff628ab"}}
